There is no need for the team to split up since the yellow victims require three people to save. The search specialist is not really worth it because one person on the team will get a map of all victim locations, eliminating the need to search.

Technically, the medic could order the hammer specialists to clear specific rubble for specific victims, but that requires a lot of effort on the medics part and I imagine that there will be a lot of downtime showing people around because the medic has to stop rescuing victims and then manually guide the person to the pile of rubble which takes time.
